 caracterización diasistemática completa de estas piezas, así como nuevas hipótesis acerca de sus correlaciones.  aThere is no survey study to date that would have analyzed the history of spatial relations in Castilian Spanish, i.e. the prepositions, transitive adverbs as well as prepositional and adverbial locutions used for the spatial localization of entities. Based on an extensive corpus, this book offers a complete diasystematic characterization of these aspects and discusses new hypotheses with regard to their correlations.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aItalian philologyxStudy and teachingzGermanyzBerlin. 0aLexicographyxHistory. 0aSpace and time in languagexHistory. 0aSpace and time in language. 0aSpanish languagexHistory. 0aSpanish languagexParts of speech. 4aGrammatikalisierung (Adverben). 4aPräpositionssysteme. 4aRäumliche Lokalisierung. 4aSprachgeschichte/Spanisch. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGrammaticalization (Adverbs).  aHistory of the Spanish Language.  aPrepositional Systems.  aSpatial Localization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2016z9783110485257oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831104565920 cprintz978311045271640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045851040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110458510423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110458510/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus De